Our mission is to make a complex world simpler\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql through technology. We aim to achieve this mission through our two-pillar strategy: strengthening our mobile foundation\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and leading in artificial intelligence (AI).\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our business currently consists of two segments, Baidu Core and iQIYI. Baidu Core is primarily comprised of\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql keyword-based marketing services, which target and are triggered by internet users\u8217? search queries. These services\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql include pay-for-performance, or P4P, services and other online marketing services and AI-enabled new business\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql initiatives. iQIYI is an innovative market-leading online entertainment service in China. iQIYI\u8217?s platform features\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql highly popular original content, as well as a comprehensive selection of professionally produced and partner-generated\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql content.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our website Baidu.com is the largest website in China and the fourth largest website globally, as measured by average\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql daily visitors and page views as of January 2018, according to Alexa.com, an internet analytics firm. We are\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql China\u8217?s top search engine in terms of number of search queries conducted, according to Analysys. In addition, our\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8220?Baidu\u8221? brand is one of the highest ranking brands in China in BrandZ Top 100 Most Valuable Chinese\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Brands 2017, a study published by Millward Brown Optimor, a brand strategy research company.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We conduct our operations primarily in China. Revenues generated from our operations in China accounted for\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql approximately 98.9%, 97.8% and 97.8% of our total revenues in 2015, 2016 and 2017, respectively.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb396\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql We serve four types of online participants:\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb132\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Users.\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~We aspire to provide the best experience to our users. To enrich user experience, we provide a broad range of\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql products and services accessible through PCs and mobile devices. We offer search and other services on our Baidu\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql platform that enables users to be connected to relevant information online, including web pages, news, images, documents,\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql multimedia files and services, through links provided on our website and apps. We have invested in advanced technology\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql such as AI to enhance user experience and deepen user engagement.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Customers.\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~We deliver online marketing services to a diverse customer base operating in a variety of industries. In\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 2017, we had approximately 775,000 active online marketing customers. The online marketing customers consist of SMEs,\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql large domestic businesses and multinational companies. Our customer base is diversified in terms of industries and\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql geographical locations. The defined industries in which our customers operate include retail and ecommerce, network\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql service, medical and healthcare, franchise investment, financial services, education, online games, transportation,\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql construction and decoration, and business services. Customers in our top five industries contributed approximately 50% of\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql our total online marketing revenues in 2017. \par\pard\plain\fs16 \par\pard\plain\fs16\par\pard\plain\brdrb\brdrs\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-5 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Although we have customers located throughout China, we have a more active and larger customer base in the coastal\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql regions, reflecting the current general economic demographics in China.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Customers for iQIYI primarily consist of advertisers, who are counted as part of our online marketing customers, and\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql membership subscribers of online video contents.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We reach and serve our customers through our direct sales force as well as a network of third-party distributors\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql across China. As many of our customers are SMEs, we use distributors to help us identify potential SME customers,\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql collect payments and assist SMEs in setting up accounts with us and using our online marketing services. We have also\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql engaged third-party agencies to identify and reach potential customers outside of China. Customers use our products and\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql services through PCs and mobile devices. Mobile revenues accounted for 73.1% of our total revenues in 2017.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Since early May 2016, we have proactively implemented higher customer verification standards to improve customer\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql quality and enhance user experience. While the verification initiative had a short term impact on our business, we believe\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the higher standards contribute to a healthier and more sustainable business for the long term.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Baidu Union Members\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql .\~Baidu Union consists of a large number of third-party web content, software and mobile app\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql providers. Baidu Union members can display on their properties our customers\u8217? promotional links that match the\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql content of such members\u8217? properties. Some Baidu Union members also embed some of our products and services\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql onto their properties. We allow Baidu Union members to provide high-quality and relevant search results to their users\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql without the cost of building and maintaining advanced search capabilities in-house and to monetize their traffic through\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql revenue sharing arrangements with us. We reward Baidu Union members through revenue-sharing arrangements. As a\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql result of our continued effort to optimize the quality of Baidu Union members, the revenues contributed by Baidu Union\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql members increased in 2017, along with the growth of revenues generated by our own properties.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Content Providers.\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our content providers mainly consist of video copyright holders, apps owners who list their apps\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql on our app store for users to download, users who contribute their valuable and copyrighted content to our products, and\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql publishers who share their content through Baijiahao accounts. We provide these content providers with a broad platform\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql for them to present their content, and they contribute rich contents and resources to our content ecosystem. If we generate\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql revenue from utilizing third-party content, we will purchase these content or share revenue with the content providers\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql based on the terms of pre-agreed contracts.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb396\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Technology and people are critical to our long-term success:\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb132\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Technology\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql . We focus on technology and innovation. To stay at the forefront of the internet industry and to achieve\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql long-term growth and success, we invest heavily in research and development. We operate five research labs under the\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql umbrella of Baidu Research, the Institute of Deep Learning, Silicon Valley AI Lab, Big Data Lab, Business Intelligence\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Lab, and Robotics and Autonomous Driving Lab. We established the Institute of Deep Learning in January 2013. We\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql opened the Silicon Valley AI Lab in May 2014, enhancing our research and development capabilities in Silicon Valley. In\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql August 2014, we and the United Nations announced and started strategic cooperation and jointly established the Big Data\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Lab. In January 2018, we established the Business Intelligence Lab and the Robotics and Autonomous Driving Lab\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql focusing on efficient data analysis and robotics.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We have developed a proprietary technological infrastructure which consists of technologies for web search, P4P,\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql large-scale systems, AI and autonomous driving. Our established infrastructure serves as the backbone for our PC, mobile\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and AI platforms. \par\pard\plain\fs16 \par\pard\plain\fs16\par\pard\plain\brdrb\brdrs\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-6 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We have been investing in AI for a number of years. By 2017, we had integrated our core technologies, including\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql natural language processing, knowledge graph, deep learning, speech, image and big data, to establish our AI technology\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql platform group (AIG). In the field of fundamental research, AIG has developed AI core technologies, such as natural\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql language processing, knowledge graph, user profile, speech technology, vision technology and deep learning technology.\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql AIG has also developed technologies including robot vision, 3D vision and edge computing. AIG powers our core\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql business, and has opened up its core AI competences with more than 90 AI capabilities and solutions to help developers\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and partners innovate apps and jointly build a technological ecosystem. AIG is also exploring ways to apply AI\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql technologies and accelerate the commercialization of AI products.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We believe autonomous driving is an important area for future growth. In 2017, we launched Apollo, our open source\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql autonomous driving platform. Apollo has been designated by China\u8217?s central government as the national\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql autonomous driving platform. To date, we have been working with over 90 global and domestic industry partners to build\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql our ecosystem to support autonomous driving. We expect that commercial production of vehicles using Apollo will start\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql mid-2018, with more to follow in the subsequent years.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql People\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql . We have a visionary and experienced management team. Under their leadership, we have developed a strong\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql company culture that encourages individual thinking and creativity, continuous self-improvement and strong commitment\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql to providing the best experience to our users and customers. We value our employees and provide abundant opportunities\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql for training, responsibility and career advancement in our organization.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb396\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql We have a robust business model:\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb132\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Baidu Core\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql . We generate revenue from Baidu Core mainly by providing keyword-based marketing services, which\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql target and are triggered by internet users\u8217? search queries, including primarily P4P services, other online marketing\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql services and AI-enabled new business initiatives. We expect that we will continue to earn a majority of our revenues from\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Baidu Core. Our P4P services account for a majority of our revenues from Baidu Core. Our P4P platform is an online\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql marketplace that introduces internet search users to customers, who pay us a fee based on click-throughs for priority\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql placement of their links in the search results. Besides the traditional auction-based P4P services, revenues from online\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql marketing services through Baidu Feed have grown rapidly since it was launched in 2016. Our feed platform helps\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql customers target relevant feed users, and customers pay us based on a cost per click basis for in-feed marketing or ad\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql displays of their products. We also provide our customers with other performance-based and display-based online\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql marketing services. Apart from the online marketing services, a majority of other revenues from Baidu Core are derived\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql from our provision of financial services, which provide installment payment services to consumers and wealth management\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql services to third-party investors.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql iQIYI\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql . iQIYI\u8217?s platform features highly popular original content, as well as a comprehensive selection of\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql professionally produced and partner-generated content. iQIYI derives a majority of its revenues from membership services\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and online advertising services. For membership services, iQIYI offers membership packages that allow the members to\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql have access to its premium content, certain commercial skipping and other viewing privileges, and higher community status\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql in iQIYI Paopao social platform. iQIYI also generates a small portion of membership services revenue from on-demand\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql content purchased by users. iQIYI\u8217?s online advertising services are in the form of brand advertising and in-feed\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql advertising.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Revenue, Profit and Cash Flow\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql . We have grown significantly by focusing on the organic growth of our core\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql business, complemented by strategic investments and acquisitions. Our total revenues in 2017 were RMB84.8\~billion\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql (US$13.0 billion), a 20.2% increase over 2016. Our operating profit in 2017 was RMB15.7\~billion (US$2.4 billion), a\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 56.1% increase over 2016. Our net income attributable to Baidu, Inc. was RMB18.3\~billion (US$2.8 billion) in 2017,\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql compared to RMB11.6\~billion in 2016. In 2017, we generated \par\pard\plain\fs16 \par\pard\plain\fs16\par\pard\plain\brdrb\brdrs\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-7 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql RMB32.9 billion (US$5.1 billion) net cash from operating activities. As of December\~31, 2017, we held a total of\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql RMB100.5 billion (US$15.4 billion) in cash and cash equivalents and short-term investments.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Potential Baidu Finance Disposal\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb132\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our board of directors has authorized our management to explore a possible disposal of Baidu financial service\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql business, or Baidu Finance, which provides consumer credit, wealth management and other financial services. We are\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql currently considering disposing of a majority equity stake in Baidu Finance, after which we will not have effective control\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql of Baidu Finance. We may enter into business cooperation arrangements with Baidu Finance after we cease to be its parent\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql company. Assuming the successful completion of the transaction, it is expected that Baidu Finance will be deconsolidated\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql from our consolidated financial statements. Our management is in the process of discussing with potential investors and\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql evaluating more detailed plans. Any such plans will be subject to our board\u8217?s review, consideration and final\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql approval. There can be no assurance that the disposal will be completed, or the terms or timing thereof.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql As of December\~31, 2017, total assets and total liabilities of Baidu Finance were RMB50.9 billion (US$7.8 billion)\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and RMB42.0 billion (US$6.5 billion), respectively. For the year ended December\~31, 2017, gross interest income and\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql interest costs recognized by Baidu Finance were RMB3.5 billion (US$543 million) and RMB1.9 billion (US$288 million),\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql respectively, and the impact of Baidu Finance to our consolidated net income was not material.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Ratio of Earnings to Fixed Charges\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb132\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The following table sets forth our unaudited consolidated ratio of earnings to fixed charges for each of the periods\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql indicated using financial information extracted, where applicable, from our audited consolidated financial statements. {\trowd\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx6295\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx6482\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx6652\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx7022\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx7112\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx7299\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx7469\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx7839\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx7929\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx8116\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx8286\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx8656\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx8746\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx8933\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx9103\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx9373\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx9463\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx9650\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx9820\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx10189\clvertalb\clshdng100\clcfpat11\clcbpat11\cellx10280\trrh248\row}}}\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb264\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The ratio of earnings to fixed charges is calculated by dividing earnings by fixed charges. The term\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8220?earnings\u8221? means the sum of (a)\~pre-tax income from continuing operations before adjustment for income or\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql loss from equity investees and (b)\~fixed charges, less the interest capitalized and the accretion of the carrying value of the\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql redeemable equity interests of the consolidated subsidiaries. The term \u8220?fixed charges\u8221? means the sum of the\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql following: (a)\~interest charges, (b)\~amortization of debt issuance costs and discounts related to indebtedness, (c)\~an estimate\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql of the interest within rental expense, and (d)\~the accretion of the carrying value of redeemable equity interests attributable\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql to the subsidiaries\u8217? unaffiliated holders of those equity interests.\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Corporate Information\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\sb132\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We were incorporated in the Cayman Islands in January 2000. We conduct our operations in China principally\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql through our wholly owned subsidiaries in China. Our American depositary shares, ten of which represent one Class\~A ordinary share, par value US$0.00005 per\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql share, of our company, currently trade on The NASDAQ Global Select Market under the symbol \u8220?BIDU.\u8221? \par\pard\plain\fs16 \par\pard\plain\fs16\par\pard\plain\brdrb\brdrs\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-8 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\li22\ri-22\fi440\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our principal executive offices are located at Baidu Campus, No.\~10 Shangdi 10th Street, Haidian District, Beijing\plain\li22\ri-22\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 100085, the People\u8217?s Republic of China. Accordingly, you may not be able to reinvest the amount received upon redemption in a\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql comparable security at an effective interest rate as high as that of the Notes.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Our credit ratings may not reflect all risks of your investments in the Notes.\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our credit ratings are an assessment by rating agencies of our ability to pay our debts when due. \~ \par\pard\plain {\trowd\cellx323\cellx10800\trrh1188 \pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs16\ql (1)\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs16\ql To supplement our consolidated financial results presented in accordance with U.S. GAAP, we use adjusted EBITDA, a non-GAAP financial measure, in\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs16\ql evaluating our performance and liquidity. We define adjusted EBITDA as operating profit excluding depreciation, amortization (excluding the amortization\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs16\ql of licensed copyrights of iQIYI) and share-based compensation expenses. The presentation of this non-GAAP financial measure is not intended to be\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs16\ql considered in isolation or as a substitute for the financial information prepared and presented in accordance with U.S. GAAP. In addition, our adjusted\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs16\ql EBITDA may not be comparable to EBITDA, adjusted EBITDA or similarly titled measures utilized by other companies since such other companies may\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs16\ql not calculate this non-GAAP financial measure in the same manner as we do.\cell{ {\trowd\cellx323\cellx10800\trrh1188\row}}}\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We believe that adjusted EBITDA provides meaningful supplemental information regarding our performance and liquidity\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql by excluding certain expenses, particularly share-based compensation expenses, that may not be indicative of our operating\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql performance or financial condition from a cash perspective. We believe that both our management and investors benefit from\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql referring to this non-GAAP financial measure in assessing our performance and when planning and forecasting future periods.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql This non-GAAP financial measure also facilitates our management\u8217?s internal comparisons to our historical performance\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and liquidity. We have computed adjusted EBITDA using the same consistent method from quarter to quarter since April\~1, 2006.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We believe that this non-GAAP financial measure is useful to investors in allowing for greater transparency with respect to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql supplemental information used by our management in its financial and operational decision making. A limitation of using\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql adjusted EBITDA is that this non-GAAP measure excludes interest, taxes, depreciation, amortization (excluding amortization of\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql licensed copyrights of iQIYI), and share-based compensation charges that have been and will continue to be for the foreseeable\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql future significant expense items in our results of operations. Another limitation of using adjusted EBITDA is that it does not\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql include all items that impact our net cash provided by operating activities for the period. Our management compensates for these\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql limitations by providing specific information regarding the GAAP amounts excluded from adjusted EBITDA.\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql The\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql Notes will be issued under and governed by the indenture dated as of November\~28, 2012, as supplemented by the sixth\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql supplemental indenture to be dated as of March 29, 2018 (as so supplemented, the \u8220?indenture\u8221?), between us and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql The Bank of New York Mellon, as trustee (the \u8220?trustee\u8221?). The following description of certain material terms of the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql Notes is subject to, and is qualified in its entirety by reference to, the indenture, including definitions of specified terms used in\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql the indenture, and to the Trust Indenture Act of 1939, as amended. We urge you to read the indenture because it, and not this\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql description, defines your rights as a beneficial holder of the Notes. A form of the indenture has been filed as an exhibit to the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql registration statement of which this prospectus supplement and the accompanying prospectus form a part. You may also request\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql copies of the indenture from us at our address set forth under \u8220?Where You Can Find More Information\u8221? in the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql accompanying prospectus. This summary supplements the description of the debt securities in the accompanying prospectus and,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql to the extent it is inconsistent, replaces the description in the accompanying prospectus.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql In this description, references to the \u8220?Company,\u8221? \u8220?we,\u8221? \u8220?us\u8221? or \u8220?our\u8221?\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql mean Baidu, Inc. only and do not include any of our Subsidiaries or Consolidated Affiliated Entities, unless the context otherwise\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql requires.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql General\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The 2023 Notes and the 2028 Notes will each constitute a series of securities under the indenture. The 2023 Notes will\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql initially be issued in an aggregate principal amount of US$1,000,000,000 and will mature on September 29, 2023, and the 2028\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Notes will initially be issued in an aggregate principal amount of US$500,000,000 and will mature on March 29, 2028, unless the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 2023 Notes or the 2028 Notes, as the case may be, are redeemed prior to their maturity pursuant to the indenture and the terms\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql thereof. The 2023 Notes will bear interest at the rate of 3.875% per annum and the 2028 Notes will bear interest at the rate of\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 4.375% per annum. Interest on the Notes will accrue from March 29, 2018 and will be payable semi-annually in arrears on\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql March 29 and September 29 of each year, beginning on September 29, 2018, to the persons in whose names the Notes are\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql registered at the close of business on the preceding March 14 and September 14, respectively, which we refer to as the record\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql dates. At maturity, the Notes are payable at their principal amount plus accrued and unpaid interest thereon. In any case where\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the payment of principal of, premium (if any) or interest on the Notes is due on a date that is not a Business Day (as defined\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql under the heading \u8220?Optional Redemption\u8221? below), then payment of principal of, premium (if any) or interest on the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Notes, as the case may be, shall be made on the next succeeding Business Day and no interest shall accrue with respect to such\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql payment for the period from and after such date that is not a Business Day to such next succeeding Business Day. Interest shall\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql be calculated on the basis of a 360-day year consisting of twelve 30-day months.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The Notes shall be denominated in minimum principal amounts of US$200,000 and in integral multiples of US$1,000 in\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql excess thereof. The Notes will be issued in global registered form.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Ranking\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The Notes will be our senior unsecured obligations issued under the indenture. The Notes will rank senior in right of\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql payment to all of our existing and future obligations expressly subordinated in right of payment to the Notes and rank at least\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql equal in right of payment with all of our existing and future unsecured and unsubordinated obligations (subject to any priority\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql rights pursuant to applicable law). However, the Notes will be effectively subordinated to all of our existing and future secured\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql obligations, to the extent of the value of the assets serving as security therefor, and be structurally subordinated to all existing\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and future obligations and other liabilities of our Controlled Entities.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Issuance of Additional Notes\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We may, from time to time, without the consent of the holders of the Notes, create and issue additional Notes having the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql same terms and conditions as any series of the Notes in all respects (or in all respects except for\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-23 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the issue date, the issue price and the first payment of interest). Additional Notes issued in this manner will be consolidated with\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the previously outstanding Notes of the relevant series to constitute a single series of the Notes of such series. the remaining term of the Notes of the applicable series to be redeemed.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8220?Comparable Treasury Price\u8221? means, with respect to any redemption date, (1)\~the average of the Reference\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Treasury Dealer Quotations for such redemption date, after excluding the highest and lowest of such Reference Treasury Dealer\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Quotations, or (2)\~if we obtain fewer than three such Reference Treasury Dealer Quotations, the average of all quotations\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql obtained.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8220?Independent Investment Banker\u8221? means one of the Reference Treasury Dealers appointed by us.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql selected by us in good faith.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8220?Reference Treasury Dealer Quotation\u8221? means, with respect to each Reference Treasury Dealer and The laws of some\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql states require that certain purchasers of securities take physical delivery of such securities in definitive form. Such limits and such\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql laws may impair the ability to own, transfer or pledge beneficial interests in the global notes.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql You, as the beneficial owner of Notes, will not receive certificates representing ownership interests in the global notes,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql except in the following limited circumstances: (1)\~DTC notifies us that it is unwilling or unable to continue as depositary or if\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql DTC ceases to be eligible under the indenture and we do not appoint a successor depositary within 90 days; (2)\~we determine\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql that the Notes will no longer be represented by global notes and execute and deliver to the trustee an officers\u8217? certificate\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql to such effect; or (3)\~an event of default with respect to the Notes will have occurred and be continuing. These certificated Notes\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql will be registered in such name or names as DTC will instruct the trustee and the agents. It is expected that such instructions\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql may be based upon directions received by DTC from participants with respect to ownership of beneficial interests in global notes.\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-31 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql So long as DTC or its nominee is the registered owner and holder of the global notes, DTC or its nominee, as the case may\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql be, will be considered the sole owner or holder of the Notes represented by the global notes for all purposes under the indenture\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql relating to the Notes. Except as provided above, you, as the beneficial owner of interests in the global notes, will not be entitled\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql to have Notes registered in your name, will not receive or be entitled to receive physical delivery of Notes in definitive form and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql will not be considered the owner or holder thereof under the indenture. Accordingly, you, as the beneficial owner, must rely on\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the procedures of DTC and, if you are not a DTC participant, on the procedures of the DTC participants through which you own\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql your interest, to exercise any rights of a holder under the indenture.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Neither we, the trustee, nor any other agent of ours or agent of the trustee will have any responsibility or liability for any\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql aspect of the records relating to, or payments made on account of, beneficial ownership interests in global notes or for\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql maintaining, supervising or reviewing any records relating to the beneficial ownership interests. DTC\u8217?s practice is to credit\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the accounts of DTC\u8217?s direct participants with payment in amounts proportionate to their respective holdings in principal\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql amount of beneficial interest in a security as shown on the records of DTC, unless DTC has reason to believe that it will not\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql receive payment on the payment date. any other aspect of the relationship between DTC\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and its participants or the relationship between those participants and the owners of beneficial interests in a global securities\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql certificate held through those participants; or the maintenance, supervision or review of any of DTC\u8217?s records relating to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql those beneficial ownership interests.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Conveyance of notices and other communications by DTC to direct participants, by direct participants to indirect\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql participants, and by direct participants and indirect participants to beneficial owners will be governed by arrangements among\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql them, subject to any statutory or regulatory requirements as may be in effect from time to time.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We have been informed that, under DTC\u8217?s existing practices, if we request any action of holders of senior notes, or\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql an owner of a beneficial interest in a global security such as you desires to take any action which a holder of the Notes is\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql entitled to take under the indenture, DTC would authorize the direct participants holding the relevant beneficial interests to take\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql such action, and those direct participants and any indirect participants would authorize beneficial owners owning through those\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql direct and indirect participants to take such action or would otherwise act upon the instructions of beneficial owners owning\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql through them.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Clearstream and Euroclear have provided us with the following information:\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Clearstream\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Clearstream is incorporated under the laws of Luxembourg as a professional depositary. Clearstream holds securities for its\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql participating organizations and facilitates the clearance and settlement of securities transactions between Clearstream participants\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql through electronic book-entry changes in accounts of Clearstream participants, thereby eliminating the need for physical\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql movement of certificates. Clearstream provides to Clearstream participants, among other things, services for safekeeping,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql administration, clearance and settlement of internationally traded securities and securities lending and borrowing. The\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql discussion is a general summary of present law, which is subject to prospective and retroactive change. It is not intended as tax\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql advice, does not consider any investor\u8217?s particular circumstances, and does not consider tax consequences other than those\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql arising under Cayman Islands law.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Under existing Cayman Islands law, payments of interest and principal on the Notes will not be subject to taxation in the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Cayman Islands and no withholding will be required on the payment of interest and principal to any holder of the Notes, nor will\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql gains derived from the disposal of the Notes be subject to Cayman Islands income or corporation tax. The Cayman Islands\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql currently have no income, corporation or capital gains tax and no estate duty, inheritance tax or gift tax. No stamp duty is\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql payable in respect of the issue of the Notes. An instrument of transfer in respect of a Note is stampable if executed in or brought\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql into the Cayman Islands.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql PRC Taxation\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The following is a summary of certain PRC tax consequences of the purchase, ownership and disposition of Notes to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql non-resident enterprises and non-resident individuals. It is based upon applicable laws, rules and regulations in effect as of the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql date of this prospectus supplement, all of which are subject to change (possibly with retroactive effect). This discussion does not\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql purport to be a comprehensive description of all the tax considerations that may be relevant to a decision to purchase, own or\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql dispose of the Notes and does not purport to deal with consequences applicable to all categories of investors, some of which may\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql be subject to special rules. Persons considering the purchase of Notes should consult their own tax advisors concerning the tax\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql consequences of the purchase, ownership and disposition of Notes, including such possible consequences under the laws of their\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql country of citizenship, residence or domicile.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql If we are considered a PRC resident enterprise under the PRC Enterprise Income Tax Law, holders of Notes who are\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql non-resident enterprises may be subject to PRC withholding tax on interest paid by us or PRC enterprise income tax on any\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql gains realized from the transfer of Notes, if such income is considered to be derived from sources within the PRC, at a rate of\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 10% (or lower rate if available under an applicable tax treaty), provided that such non-resident enterprise investor (i)\~has no\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql establishment or premises in the PRC, or (ii)\~has an establishment or premises in the PRC but its income derived from the PRC\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql has no real connection with such establishment or premises. Furthermore, if we are considered a PRC resident enterprise and the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql relevant PRC tax authorities consider interest we pay on the Notes or any gains realized from the transfer of Notes to be income\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql derived from sources within the PRC, such interest earned by non-resident individuals may be subject to PRC withholding tax\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and such gain realized by non-resident individuals may be subject to PRC individual income tax, in each case at a rate of 20%\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql (or lower rate if available under an applicable tax treaty). In addition, if we are considered a PRC resident enterprise under the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql PRC Enterprise Income Tax Law, interest payable by us to non-resident holders of the Notes may be subject to PRC\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql value-added tax at a rate of 6% and related local levies, including educational surtax and urban maintenance and construction tax\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql at a rate of up to 0.72%.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql If we are not deemed a PRC resident enterprise, non-resident enterprise and non-resident individual holders of Notes will\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql not be subject to PRC income tax on any payments of interest on, or gains from the transfer of, Notes.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql U.S. Federal Income Tax Considerations\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The following discussion is a summary of U.S. federal income tax considerations under present law of the ownership and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql disposition of the Notes. Moreover, this discussion does not address any\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql foreign, state or local tax considerations, any aspect of the Medicare tax on net investment income or any aspect of U.S. federal\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql non-income tax laws, such as gift or estate tax laws.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql PROSPECTIVE INVESTORS ARE URGED TO CONSULT THEIR OWN TAX ADVISORS CONCERNING THE\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql APPLICATION OF THE U.S. FEDERAL INCOME TAX LAWS TO THEIR PARTICULAR CIRCUMSTANCES AS WELL\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql AS ANY STATE, LOCAL OR FOREIGN TAX CONSEQUENCES TO THEM OF THE OWNERSHIP AND DISPOSITION OF\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql THE NOTES.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The discussion below regarding U.S. federal income tax consequences is based upon the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql amended, U.S. Treasury regulations promulgated thereunder as well as administrative rulings or pronouncements or judicial\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql decisions thereof, all as of the date hereof. All of the foregoing authorities are subject to change, which change could apply\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql retroactively and could affect the tax considerations described below.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql If a partnership or other entity treated as a partnership for U.S. federal income tax purposes holds the Notes, the tax\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql treatment of a partner will generally depend upon the status of the partner and the activities of the partnership. If you are a\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql partnership or other entity treated as a partnership for U.S. federal income tax purposes holding the Notes or a partner therein,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql you are urged to consult your tax advisor.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Interest Payments\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Payments of stated interest on the Notes will be includible in your gross income as ordinary interest income at the time you\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql receive or accrue such amounts (in accordance with your regular method of tax accounting).\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Interest on the Notes will constitute foreign-source income for U.S. federal income tax purposes. For foreign tax credit\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql limitation purposes, interest on the Notes will generally constitute passive income.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql As described in \u8220?\u8212?PRC Taxation,\u8221? if we are deemed to be a PRC resident enterprise under the PRC\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Enterprise Income Tax Law, payments of interest in respect of the Notes may be subject to PRC withholding\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-36 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql taxes. For U.S. federal income tax purposes, the amount of interest includible in taxable income would include any amounts\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql withheld in respect of PRC taxes. If PRC withholding taxes apply to interest paid to you with respect to the Notes, you may be\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql able to obtain a reduced rate of PRC withholding taxes under the income tax treaty between the United States and the PRC (the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8220?U.S.-PRC Income Tax Treaty\u8221?) if certain requirements are met. In addition, subject to certain conditions and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql limitations, PRC withholding taxes on interest that is non-refundable under the U.S.-PRC Income Tax Treaty may be treated as\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql foreign taxes eligible for credit against your U.S. federal income tax liability. If you do not elect to claim a foreign tax credit,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql you may instead claim a deduction for U.S. federal income tax purposes in respect of such withholding, but only for a year in\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql which you elect to do so for all creditable foreign income taxes. You are urged to consult your tax advisor regarding the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql deductibility and creditability of any PRC tax.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Any Additional Amounts paid pursuant to the obligations described under \u8220?Description of the Notes\u8212?Payment\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql of Additional Amounts\u8221? will be treated as foreign-source ordinary interest income.\par\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Sale, Exchange, Redemption and Other Disposition of the Notes\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Upon the sale, exchange, redemption or other disposition of the Notes, you will recognize taxable gain or loss equal to the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql difference, if any, between the amount realized on the sale, exchange, redemption or other disposition (other than amounts\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql attributable to accrued but unpaid interest which will be treated as ordinary interest income) and your adjusted tax basis in such\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Notes. Your adjusted tax basis in the Notes will generally equal the cost of such Notes. Any such gain or loss will generally be\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql capital gain or loss and will be long-term capital gain or loss if at the time of sale, exchange, redemption or other disposition\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql you held the Notes for more than one year. The deductibility of capital losses is subject to certain limitations.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql As described in \u8220?\u8212?PRC Taxation,\u8221? if we are deemed to be a PRC resident enterprise under the PRC\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Enterprise Income Tax Law, gains from the disposition of Notes may be subject to PRC income taxes. You may use foreign tax\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql credits to offset only the portion of your U.S. tax liability considered to be attributable to foreign-source income. Generally, gain\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql or loss from the disposition of Notes will be U.S.-source for foreign tax credit limitation purposes, which will generally limit the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql availability of foreign tax credits. However, if you are eligible for the benefits of the U.S.-PRC Income Tax Treaty, you may be\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql able to elect to treat such gain as PRC source income under the U.S.-PRC Income Tax Treaty. You are urged to consult your tax\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql advisor regarding your eligibility for benefits under the U.S.-PRC Income Tax Treaty and the creditability of any PRC tax in\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql your particular circumstances if you are so eligible.\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc S-37 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}{\*\bkmkstart supprom434211_14_12148241}{\*\bkmkend supprom434211_14_12148241}\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\b\qc UNDERWRITING\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Subject to the terms and conditions contained in the underwriting agreement, dated as of the date of this prospectus\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql supplement between us and the underwriters named below, for whom Goldman Sachs (Asia) L.L.C., J.P. Over-allotment involves sales in excess of the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql offering size, which creates a short position. Stabilizing transactions permit bids to purchase the underlying security so long as\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the stabilizing bids do not exceed a specified maximum. Covering transactions involve purchase of the Notes in the open market\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql after the distribution has been completed in order to cover short positions. Penalty bids permit the underwriters to reclaim a\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql selling concession from a dealer when the Notes originally sold by such dealer are purchased in a stabilizing transaction or a\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql covering transaction to cover short positions. Neither we nor the underwriters make any representation or prediction as to the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql direction or magnitude of any effect that the transactions described above may have on the price of the Notes. As a technology-based media company, we aim to provide\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the best and most equitable way for people to find what they are looking for. We provide our users with many channels to access\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql information and services. In addition to serving individual internet search users, we provide an effective platform for businesses\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql to reach potential customers.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our business currently consists of keyword-based marketing services targeted at and triggered by internet users\u8217?\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql search queries, which mainly include our pay-for-performance, or P4P, services and other online marketing services, artificial\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql intelligence (AI)-enabled new business initiatives and online video business.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\i\ql Baidu.com\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql website is the largest website in China and the fourth largest website globally, as measured by average daily\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql visitors and page views during the three-month period preceding the date of this prospectus, according to Alexa.com, an internet\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql analytics firm. We are the largest internet search provider in China, accounting for 84% of revenues of the PC and mobile search\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql market in China in the three months ended March\~31, 2017, according to Analysys International, a market research firm. We are\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the top Chinese search engine in terms of combined PC and mobile search page views in the three months ended March\~31,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 2017, according to StatCounter, an internet analytics firm. In addition, our \u8220?Baidu\u8221? brand is one of the highest\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql ranking brands in China in BrandZ Top 50 Most Valuable Chinese Brands 2016, a study published by Millward Brown Optimor,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql a brand strategy research company.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We conduct our operations primarily in China. Revenues generated from our operations in China accounted for\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql approximately 99.5%, 98.9% and 97.8% of our total revenues in 2014, 2015 and 2016, respectively.\par\pard\plain\li88\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql We serve four types of online participants:\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Users.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~We aspire to provide the best experience to our users. To enrich user experience, we provide a broad range of\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql products and services accessible through PCs and mobile devices. We offer Chinese language search on our Baidu platform that\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql enables users to find relevant information online, including web pages, news, images, documents and multimedia files, through\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql links provided on our website. We launched Baidu Newsfeed in 2016 to offer users personalized newsfeed to meet their personal\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql interests as reflected in their past online behaviors, such as search and browsing, and their demographics. In addition,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql iQiyi\u8217?s mobile application has continued to maintain its industry leadership with 129\~million daily active users, 490\~million\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql monthly active users, and 342\~billion minutes monthly user time in March 2017, according to iResearch, a market research firm.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Customers.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~We deliver online marketing services to a diverse customer base operating in a variety of industries. The\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql number of our active online marketing customers grew from approximately 596,000 in 2012 to approximately 982,000 in 2016.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Consistent with previously reported numbers, the number of active online marketing customers excluded those for our\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql group-buying and delivery related businesses. Our online marketing customers consist of small to medium-sized enterprises, or\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql SMEs, throughout China, large domestic companies and Chinese divisions and subsidiaries of large, multinational companies. We\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql have a diverse customer base in terms of industries and geographical locations. The top industries in which our customers operate\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql in terms of revenue contribution include retail and ecommerce, local services, medical and healthcare, network services, financial\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql services, education, online games, transportation, construction and decoration, and business services. Customers in our top five\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql industries contributed approximately 50% of our total online marketing revenues in 2016. Although we have customers located\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql throughout China, we have a more active and larger customer base in coastal regions, reflecting the current general economic\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql demographics in China. Our customers also include local merchants that act as advertisers or service providers covering\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql businesses such as restaurants, hotels and cinemas, and advertisers of iQiyi, who are counted as part of our online marketing\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql customers, and subscription users of online video contents.\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc 3 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We reach and serve our customers through our direct sales force as well as a network of third-party distributors across\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql China. As many of our customers are SMEs, we use distributors to help us identify potential SME customers, collect payments\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and assist SMEs in setting up accounts with us and using our online marketing services. We have also engaged third-party\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql agencies to identify and reach potential customers outside of China. Customers use our products and services through PCs and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql mobile devices. Mobile revenues represented 70.0% of our total revenues in the three months ended March 31, 2017.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Since early May 2016, we have been implementing new measures to further improve customer quality and foster a healthy\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql environment to enhance user experience and drive long-term sustainable growth. We have taken proactive measures requiring all\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql customers on our platform to submit Internet Content Provider (ICP) licenses and verify enterprise bank accounts. The\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql implementation of new and stricter regulations on online marketing and our self-imposed proactive measures will have a\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql short-term impact on our business. We believe these measures will be beneficial in the long term, and we remain confident in\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql our long-term outlook, underpinned by our fundamental value proposition of search and our ongoing investments in technology.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Baidu Union Members\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql .\~Baidu Union consists of a large number of third-party web content, software and mobile\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql application providers. Baidu Union members can display on their properties our customers\u8217? promotional links that match\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the content of such members\u8217? properties. Some Baidu Union members also embed some of our products and services into\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql their properties. We allow Baidu Union members to provide high-quality and relevant search results to their users without the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql cost of building and maintaining advanced search capabilities in-house and to monetize their traffic through revenue sharing\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql arrangements with us. We reward Baidu Union members by sharing with these members revenues as a percentage of total\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql revenues recognized by us. Because we have implemented measures to deliver a better user experience and build a safer and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql more trustworthy platform for users since May 2016, the revenue contributed by Baidu Union members slightly decreased in\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql 2016.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Content Providers.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our content providers mainly consist of video copyright holders, map data owners, apps owners who list\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql their apps on our app store for users to download, users who contribute their valuable and copyrighted content to our products,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and self-media authors such as those who publish their content through Baijiahao accounts. These content providers contribute\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql rich contents and resources to our content ecosystem, and in return we provide a broad platform for them to present their content.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql If we generate revenue from utilizing third-party contents, we will purchase these contents or share revenue with the content\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql providers based on the terms of pre-agreed contracts.\par\pard\plain\li88\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Technology and people are critical to our long-term success:\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\b\i\ql Technology\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql . We focus on research and development and innovation. To stay at the forefront of the internet industry and to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql achieve long-term growth and success, we invest heavily in research and development. We operate four research labs under the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql umbrella of Baidu Research: the Augmented Reality (AR) Lab, the Silicon Valley Artificial Intelligence (AI) Lab, the Beijing\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Deep Learning Lab and the Beijing Big Data Lab. We established the Baidu Institute of Deep Learning, currently known as the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Beijing Deep Learning Lab, in January 2013. We opened the Silicon Valley AI Lab in May 2014, enhancing our research and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql development capabilities in Silicon Valley. In August 2014, we and the United Nations announced and started strategic\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql cooperation and jointly established the Big Data Lab. In January 2017, we announced the establishment of our AR Lab focusing\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql on augmented reality technology. Since September 2016, we have open-sourced our AI platform \u8220?PaddlePaddle\u8221? to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the global developer community, providing access to Baidu technology in areas of voice and image recognition, natural language\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql processing, and machine learning.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql In 2015, our autonomous driving project at the Beijing Deep Learning Lab reached a key milestone by completing rigorous\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql fully autonomous tests under a variety of complex environmental conditions. We have been recognized as one of the leading AI\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql innovators globally after investing in AI for many years. In 2016, we established our Autonomous Driving Business Unit. In\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql April 2017, we announced Project Apollo, our autonomous driving open platform.\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc 4 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We have developed a proprietary technological infrastructure which consists of technologies for web search, mobile, P4P,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql targetizement, large-scale systems, AI and autonomous driving technology. The ratio of earnings to fixed charges is calculated by dividing earnings by fixed charges. The term \u8220?earnings\u8221?\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql means the sum of (a)\~pre-tax income from continuing operations before adjustment for income or loss from equity investees and\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql (b)\~fixed charges, less the interest capitalized and the accretion of the carrying value of the redeemable equity interests of the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql consolidated subsidiaries. The term \u8220?fixed charges\u8221? means the sum of the following: (a)\~interest charges,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql (b)\~amortization of debt issuance costs and discounts related to indebtedness, (c)\~an estimate of the interest within rental expense,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql and (d)\~the accretion of the carrying value of redeemable equity interests attributable to the subsidiaries\u8217? unaffiliated\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql holders of those equity interests.\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc 10 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}{\*\bkmkstart toc377819_8_12148241}{\*\bkmkend toc377819_8_12148241}{\*\bkmkstart supprom377819_24_12148241}{\*\bkmkend supprom377819_24_12148241}\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\b\qc DESCRIPTION OF DEBT SECURITIES\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql The following is a summary of certain general terms and provisions of the debt securities and the indenture, but they are not\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql complete and are subject to, and are qualified in their entirety by reference to, all of the provisions of the indenture, which has\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql been filed as an exhibit to the registration statement of which this prospectus is a part, including the definitions of specified terms\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql used in the indenture, and to the Trust Indenture Act of 1939, as amended, or the \u8220?Trust Indenture Act.\u8221? These intermediary banks, brokers, other financial institutions and depositaries pass along\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql principal, interest, dividends and other payments, if any, on the debt securities, either because they agree to do so in their\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql customer agreements or because they are legally required to do so. This means that if you are an indirect holder, you will need to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql coordinate with the institution through which you hold your interest in a security in order to determine how the provisions\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql involving holders described in this prospectus and any prospectus supplement will actually apply to you. Instead, you would need to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql cause the institution through which you hold your interest to take those actions on your behalf. supplement.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql If you hold our debt securities in street name or through other indirect means, you should check with the institution {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh495\row}}}\pard\plain\sb396\cf1\f51\fs20\b\ql Global Securities\par\pard\plain\sb132\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql A global security is a special type of indirectly held security. If we issue debt securities in the form of global securities, the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql ultimate beneficial owners can only be indirect holders. We do this by requiring that the global security be registered in the name\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql of a financial institution we select and by requiring that the debt securities included in the global security not be transferred to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the name of any other direct holder unless the special circumstances described below occur. The financial institution that acts as\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the sole direct holder of the global security is called the \u8220?depositary.\u8221? We will not recognize you as a holder of\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the debt securities and instead will deal only with the depositary that holds the global security.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql You should be aware that if our debt securities are issued only in the form of global securities:\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs12\ql \~ \par\pard\plain \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the availability of professional and support services.\cell{ {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh248\row}}}\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql However, certain disadvantages accompany incorporation in the Cayman Islands. These disadvantages include:\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs12\ql \~ \par\pard\plain {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh495 \pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8226?\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql the Cayman Islands has a less developed body of securities laws as compared to the United States and these\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql securities laws provide significantly less protection to investors; and\cell{ {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh495\row}}}\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs12\ql \~ \par\pard\plain {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh248 \pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8226?\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Cayman Islands companies may not have standing to sue before the federal courts of the United States.\cell{ {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh248\row}}}\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Our constituent documents do not contain provisions requiring that disputes, including those arising under the securities laws\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql of the United States, between us, our officers, directors and shareholders, be arbitrated.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Substantially all of our current operations are conducted in China, and substantially all of our assets are located in China.\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql We have appointed C T Corporation System, which is located at 111 Eighth Avenue, New York, NY 10011, as our agent upon\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql whom process may be served in any action brought against us under the securities laws of the United States. A majority of our\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql directors and officers are nationals or residents of jurisdictions other than the United States and a substantial portion of their\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql assets are located outside the United States. As a result, it may be difficult for an investor to effect service of process within the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql United States upon these persons, or to enforce against us or them judgments obtained in United States courts, including\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql judgments predicated upon the civil liability provisions of the securities laws of the United States or any state in the United\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql States.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Maples and Calder (Hong Kong) LLP, our counsel as to Cayman Islands law, and Han Kun Law Offices, our counsel as to\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql PRC law, have advised us that there is uncertainty as to whether the courts of the Cayman Islands and China, respectively,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql would:\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs12\ql \~ \par\pard\plain {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh495 \pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8226?\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql recognize or enforce judgments of United States courts obtained against us or our directors or officers predicated\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql upon the civil liability provisions of the securities laws of the United States or any state in the United States; or\cell{ {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh495\row}}}\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs12\ql \~ \par\pard\plain {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh495 \pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \u8226?\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql \~\cell\pard\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql entertain original actions brought in each respective jurisdiction against us or our directors or officers predicated\plain\intbl\cf1\f51\fs20\ql upon the securities laws of the United States or any state in the United States.\cell{ {\trowd\clvertalc\cellx540\cellx1204\cellx1311\cellx10800\trrh495\row}}}\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Maples and Calder (Hong Kong) LLP has advised us that there is no statutory recognition in the Cayman Islands of\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql judgments obtained in the United States, although the courts of the Cayman Islands will in the circumstances described below,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql recognize and enforce a non-penal judgment of a foreign court of competent jurisdiction without retrial on the merits. While\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql there is no binding authority on this point, this is likely to include, in certain circumstances, a non-penal judgment of a United\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql States court imposing a monetary award based on the civil liability provisions of the U.S. federal securities laws.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Maples and Calder (Hong Kong) LLP has further advised us that a judgment obtained in the United States will be\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql recognized and enforced in the courts of the Cayman Islands at common law, without any re-examination of the merits of the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql underlying dispute, by an action commenced on the foreign judgment debt in the Grand Court of the Cayman Islands, provided\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql such judgment (1)\~is given by a foreign court of competent jurisdiction;\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql \~\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\qc 29 \page\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\pard\plain\f0\fs2\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2\brdrsp0\par\pard\plain\f0\fs4\par\par\pard\plain\ul{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK \\l "toc_12148241" }{\*\fldrslt\cf3\f52\fs16\b\ql Table of Contents}}\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql (2)\~imposes on the judgment debtor a liability to pay a liquidated sum for which the judgment has been given; (3)\~is final; (4)\~is\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql not in respect of taxes, a fine or a penalty; and (5)\~was not obtained in a manner and is not of a kind the enforcement of which\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql is contrary to natural justice or the public policy of the Cayman Islands. The Grand Court of the Cayman Islands may stay\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql proceedings if concurrent proceedings are being brought elsewhere. Neither the United States or the PRC has a treaty with the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Cayman Islands providing for reciprocal recognition and enforcement of judgments of courts of the United States or the PRC,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql respectively, in civil and commercial matters.\par\pard\plain\sb264\fi462\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Han Kun Law Offices has further advised us that the recognition and enforcement of foreign judgments are provided for\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql under the PRC Civil Procedures Law. PRC courts may recognize and enforce foreign judgments in accordance with the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql requirements of the PRC Civil Procedures Law based either on treaties between China and the country where the judgment is\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql made or on principles of reciprocity between jurisdictions. China does not have any treaties or other form of reciprocity with the\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql United States that provide for the reciprocal recognition and enforcement of foreign judgments. In addition, according to the PRC\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql Civil Procedures Law, courts in the PRC will not enforce a foreign judgment against us or our directors and officers if they\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql decide that the judgment violates the basic principles of PRC law or national sovereignty, security or public interest. As a result,\plain\cf1\f51\fs20\ql it is uncertain whether and on what basis a PRC court would enforce a judgment rendered by a court in the United States.\par\pard\plain\cf1\f51\fs16\ql
